.TH "MEDIASOURCE.SOURCEOPEN_EVENT" "3JS" "July 14, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
MediaSource.sourceopen_event \- MediaSource: sourceopen event
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Dedicated Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]sourceopen\f[B]\f[R] event is fired when a
\f[CR]MediaSource\f[R] object\(cqs \f[CR]readyState\f[R] changes to
\f[CR]\(dqopen\(dq\f[R].
This indicates that the \f[CR]MediaSource\f[R] is ready to receive data
from \f[CR]SourceBuffer\f[R] objects.
This can occur either when the \f[CR]MediaSource\f[R] object is first
attached to a media element or when the \f[CR]readyState\f[R] changes
from \f[CR]\(dqended\(dq\f[R] back to \f[CR]\(dqopen\(dq\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqsourceopen\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {});

onsourceopen = (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {};
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Handling the sourceopen event
This example sets up a \f[CR]MediaSource\f[R], connects it to a video
element, and listens for the \f[CR]sourceopen\f[R] event.
When the event fires, it adds a \f[CR]SourceBuffer\f[R] to handle the
video data, fetches the data, appends it to the buffer, and finally
revokes the object URL when the source ends.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] video = document.getElementById(\(dqmyVideo\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] mediaSource = \f[B]new\f[R] MediaSource();

video.src = URL.createObjectURL(mediaSource);

mediaSource.addEventListener(\(dqsourceopen\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(\(dqMediaSource sourceopen:\(dq, event);
  \f[I]// Add source buffers and begin adding media data.\f[R]
  \f[B]const\f[R] sourceBuffer = mediaSource.addSourceBuffer(
    \(aqvideo/mp4; codecs=\(dqavc1.42E01E\(dq\(aq,
  );
  fetch(\(dqvideo\-data.mp4\(dq)
    .then((response) \f[B]=>\f[R] response.arrayBuffer())
    .then((data) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
      sourceBuffer.appendBuffer(data);
    });
});

mediaSource.addEventListener(\(dqsourceended\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  URL.revokeObjectURL(video.src);
});
.EE
